<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - INSPECTION - SCORED ROTORS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SCORED ROTORS</title>
        <para>A scored rotor is indicated by a grooved appearance on the braking surface (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401819">Figure 19
                <xref refid="f0401819"/>
            </hotlnk>
            ).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0401819" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0401819" filename="../figg04/G0401819.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 19. Scored Rotor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>If the scoring exceeds .015 inch and the thickness of the braking surface can be kept within allowable
            limits, the rotor may be turned to restore a smooth braking surface. It is recommended that the brake pads
            be replaced.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
